.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE WIELKANOC-7 SP "25 Mar 88" 1989
.RZ "ZUREK WIELKANOCNY" "Easter Soup"
.IH "Serves 4"
.IG "2 cups" "rolled oats" "150 g"
.IG "2 cups" "warm water" "500 ml"
.IG "1 crust" "sour dough rye bread"
.IG "1\(12 lbs" "kielbasa" "700 g"
(Polish sausage)
.IG "6 cups" "water" "1.5 l"
.IG "1 Tbsp" "prepared horseradish" "15 ml"
.IG "1 tsp" "brown sugar" "5 ml"
.IG "1 tsp" "salt" "5 ml"
.IG "\(12 tsp" "pepper" "2.5 ml"
.SK 1
Mix oats and warm water.  Add bread crust.  Let stand until mixture sours,
at least 24 hours.  Strain; reserve liquid.
.SK 2
Cook sausage in water for 1 hour.  Remove sausage.  Skim off
fat.  Combine skimmed broth and oatmeal liquid.
.SK 3
Add horseradish, brown sugar, salt and pepper.  Slice sausage and add to
broth.  Bring just to boiling.
.SK 4
Serve hot with boiled potatoes and hard-cooked eggs.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
easy.
.I Time:
1 day blending, 1 hour cooking.
.I Precision:
Approximate measurement OK.
.WR
Original recipe passed down through the generations and translated from
Polish into English by
Edward Chrzanowski
MFCF, University of Waterloo, Waterloo, Ontario, Canada
